"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786258","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-13","<p>My Rt Hon Friend the member for Witham (Ms Patel) resigned as Secretary of State for International Development on 8 November. The Department was not aware of the visit in advance of it taking place.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-11-13T17:17:02.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786258/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786258/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-07","Israel: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what advice she received from officials of her Department before her visit to Israel in August 2017.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","112024"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786259","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-13","<p>My Rt Hon Friend the member for Witham (Ms Patel) resigned as Secretary of State for International Development on 8 November. The Department has not arranged any such meetings.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-11-13T17:08:32.153Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786259/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786259/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-07","Israel: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will list all her meetings with representatives of the Government of Israel since June 2017 and the dates of each such meeting.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","112025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786260","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-15","<p>On 30 October, the Lord Chancellor announced the commencement of the post-implementation review of the legal aid changes made by, and following, the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012. The review will look at the impact of recent policy changes on access to legal aid.</p><p> </p><p>The Legal Aid Agency regularly review the capacity of the legal aid market to cope with demand for legal aid and take action where a regional shortfall develops.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-11-15T16:29:57.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786260/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786260/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-07","Legal Aid Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 11 September 2017 to Question 7534, on legal aid scheme, whether he has looked more widely at the impact of recent policy changes on access to legal aid; and whether his Department will be taking steps to ensure that people in all regions can access legal aid providers.","false","Biography information for Sandy Martin","Ipswich","Sandy Martin","111932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786261","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-13","<p>The Community Rehabilitation Company (CRC) contracts do not specify that CRCs must maintain staffing numbers at a particular level. However, the contracts do contain robust provisions requiring each CRC to ensure that it employs a sufficient level of competent and appropriately trained staff. We continue to closely monitor this as part of our contract management and assurance process.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-11-13T17:08:32.103Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786261/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786261/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-07","Community Rehabilitation Companies: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 3 November 2017 to Question 109713, on staff: probation, what the minimum level of staffing required by each community rehabilitation company is to meet its obligations of a sufficient level of staff.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","112018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786262","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-17","<p>We are determined to crackdown on unacceptable behaviour and improve fans’ chances of buying tickets at a reasonable price.</p><p> </p><p>The Consumer Rights Act 2015 already includes rules about tickets offered for sale on the secondary market, and the Digital Economy Act passed earlier this year adds an additional requirement for ticket sellers to provide a unique ticket number when reselling a ticket resale, and provides the power to create a specific offence, where tickets are purchased electronically, of purchasing more tickets than the maximum permitted.</p><p> </p><p>We have provided funding for enforcement action to be taken by Trading Standards against sellers who are in breach of consumer law.</p><p> </p><p>The Competition and Markets Authority has also launched an enforcement investigation into suspected breaches of consumer protection law in the online secondary ticketing market which is hoped will drive further transparency in the secondary market.</p><p>B</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-11-17T13:22:20.413Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786262/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786262/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-11-07","Tickets: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps her Department is taking to reduce the prevalence of the resale of tickets at inflated prices for theatrical, musical and other artistic performances.","false","Biography information for Sandy Martin","Ipswich","Sandy Martin","111936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786263","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-17","<p>The Government is committed to keeping prisoners safe. The cell-sharing risk assessment process brings together all available information with the aim of identifying factors that increase the likelihood of harm by or to an offender, so that decisions about locating prisoners in shared cells are made in a way that minimises those risks. We keep the process under review and continue to work to improve the information that is available to staff making these important decisions.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-11-17T13:10:45.403Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786263/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786263/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786263/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-07","Prisoners: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of risk assessments for cell-sharing in prisons.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","111952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786264","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-15","<p>I refer the honourable member to the answer which I gave in PQ 107525, answered on 13th October 2017.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-11-15T16:30:47.033Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786264/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786264/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-07","Ministry of Justice: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he plans to answer the named day written question 107525 tabled on 12 October 2017.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","111883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786265","Department of Health","false","2017-11-16","<p>Secure setting treatment figures are currently only available for 2015-16. Figures are not available for people who requested treatment, only for those starting or already receiving treatment.</p><p>Data in secure setting statistics from the National Drug Treatment Monitoring System for England showed there were 60,254 adults in contact with drug and alcohol treatment services within secure settings during 2015-16, and most (56,803) of these were within a prison setting:</p><p><a href="http://www.nta.nhs.uk/uploads/secure-setting-statistics-from-the-national-drug-treatment-monitoring-system-2015-2016.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.nta.nhs.uk/uploads/secure-setting-statistics-from-the-national-drug-treatment-monitoring-system-2015-2016.pdf</a></p><p>There were a further 3,124 in contact with treatment services within Youth Offending Institutions and 327 within Immigration Removal Centres.</p><p> </p><p>Of all the people in contact with treatment services in secure settings in this year, there were 40,382 people starting a new treatment programme.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-11-16T13:45:10.183Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786265/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786265/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-07","Prisoners: Rehabilitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people in prison in England and Wales (a) requested and (b) received drug and alcohol treatment in each quarter for the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","111869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786266","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-16","<p>The Department publishes County Court, Family Court and Crown Court figures on defendants or parties with no (or unknown) representation. This data does not represent the number of litigants in person, however, because a party may be without representation for only part of a case or may be entitled to legal help but not full representation. Information on unrepresented defendants in Magistrates Courts is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the number of parties with and without representation in cases with at least one hearing is published in Table 9 in the Family Court Statistics Quarterly, and trend analysis since 2011 is also given. The latest edition is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/family-court-statistics-quarterly-april-to-june-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/family-court-statistics-quarterly-april-to-june-2017</a></p><p> </p><p>Figures on the number of no (or unknown) representation in the Crown Court, including trends since 2010, is published in table AC11 of the annual publication, link below:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-court-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-court-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2017</a></p><p> </p><p>Figures on the number of civil defended claims with and without representation, since 2013, are published in table 1.6 of the quarterly publication, link below:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/civil-justice-statistics-quarterly-april-to-june-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/civil-justice-statistics-quarterly-april-to-june-2017</a></p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-11-16T11:45:40.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786266/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786266/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786266/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-07","Legal Representation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people were litigants in person in England and Wales in each of the last five years in (a) civil and (b) criminal cases.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","111870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786267","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-15","<p>In each of the last five years, the Government’s expenditure on the Client and Cost Management System (CCMS) has remained within its estimates. The costs (£m) incurred in each of the last five years are set out below.</p><p> </p><p>This expenditure is representative of all aspects of the system, i.e. the LAA’s internal management and administration of CCMS, and the interface used by the legal profession.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£ 15.174</p></td><td><p>£ 7.858</p></td><td><p>£ 4.526</p></td><td><p>£ 3.995</p></td><td><p>£ 3.841</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","111872","2017-11-15T16:27:26.763Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786267/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786267/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786267/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-07","Legal Aid Scheme: Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate the Government has made of the cost of the Client and Cost Management System in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","111871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786268","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-15","<p>In each of the last five years, the Government’s expenditure on the Client and Cost Management System (CCMS) has remained within its estimates. The costs (£m) incurred in each of the last five years are set out below.</p><p> </p><p>This expenditure is representative of all aspects of the system, i.e. the LAA’s internal management and administration of CCMS, and the interface used by the legal profession.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£ 15.174</p></td><td><p>£ 7.858</p></td><td><p>£ 4.526</p></td><td><p>£ 3.995</p></td><td><p>£ 3.841</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","111871","2017-11-15T16:27:26.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786268/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786268/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786268/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-07","Legal Aid Scheme: Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much the Government has spent on the Client and Cost Management System in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","111872"
